OL,3,CGovernment spending #4m a year on
OL,4,C'unusable' prison with no inmates
OL,6,FIt has now been revealed that the
OL,7,FMinistry of Justice, through the HM
OL,8,FPrison and Probation Service (HMPPS),
OL,9,Fis locked into #4 million a year of
OL,10,Frental and security costs for the
OL,11,Fshuttered jail, potentially lasting
OL,12,Ffor the next eight years.
OL,14,FIt is also committed to paying out
OL,15,Faround #68 million for "fabric
OL,16,Fimprovements" to the prison over the
OL,17,Fcourse of the lease, which ends in
OL,18,F2033.
OL,26,@wD@XOUxD@MO]
