OL,3,CGovernment spending #4m a year on
OL,4,C'unusable' prison with no inmates
OL,6,FMPs also accused the prison service of
OL,7,Ffailing to "have a plan for when the
OL,8,Fprison will be back in use".
OL,10,F"Given HMPPS knew that radon was at
OL,11,Fthe site before signing the lease, it
OL,12,Fwas a very poor commercial decision
OL,13,Fnot to negotiate a financial safeguard
OL,14,Fin the event that it needed to
OL,15,Fpartially or fully close the prison
OL,16,Fdue to radon levels."
OL,18,FParliament heard in evidence sessions
OL,19,Flast year that high levels of radon
OL,20,Fwere first detected at the Grade II
OL,21,Flisted jail in 2020.
OL,26,@oD@LOUpD@[O]rD@AOUxD@UO]
