OL,3,CGovernment spending #4m a year on
OL,4,C'unusable' prison with no inmates
OL,6,FThe prison service argued that the new
OL,7,Flease had to be signed due to the
OL,8,Fpressure for prison places, which in
OL,9,F2022 was already at crisis levels.
OL,11,FIt agreed to #1.5 million in annual
OL,12,Frent, and did not negotiate the
OL,13,Fpossibility of early departure from
OL,14,Fthe lease ahead of December 2033.
OL,16,F"We do not accept that the prison
OL,17,Fcapacity crisis excuses such poor
OL,18,Fcommercial decisions, which have
OL,19,Fresulted in this needless waste of
OL,20,Ftaxpayers' money," said the
OL,21,Fcommittee's report.
OL,26,@xD@AOU|D@RO]
